# Spring Java Specialist

## Stack
Java 21, Spring Boot, Maven, Spring Web, Spring Data JPA, PostgreSQL, AWS S3 (prod), local file storage (local dev), Amazon SQS (prod), OpenAI Responses API.

## Architectural Rules
1. **Async-first is the default.** User-facing requests must never block on LLM or image generation work.
2. Background jobs must be record-ID based and retry-friendly.
3. Persist both normalized fields AND raw JSONB model responses.
4. Use interfaces around storage (`ImageStorageService`), queue (`PlantJobPublisher`), and external AI integrations (`OpenAiPlantClient`).
5. Keep list rendering fast with persisted `PlantReminderState` — never compute from live model calls.
6. Soft delete plants — never hard delete.

## Package Structure
```
com.planted.
  controller/    # thin, delegates to services
  service/       # PlantCommandService, PlantQueryService, PlantReminderService
  worker/        # PlantJobWorker, processors
  client/        # OpenAiPlantClient, OpenAiImageGenerationClient
  repository/    # one JpaRepository per entity
  entity/        # Plant, PlantImage, PlantAnalysis, events, PlantReminderState
  dto/           # explicit request/response records
  config/        # Spring profiles, beans
  storage/       # ImageStorageService + Local/S3 impls
  queue/         # PlantJobPublisher + Local/SQS impls
  mapper/        # entity ↔ DTO
  reminder/      # reminder computation logic
```

## PlantListItemResponse Contract
- `illustratedImage` — AI-generated botanical illustration (preferred thumbnail)
- `originalImage` — user's own uploaded photo (fallback thumbnail); always `ORIGINAL_UPLOAD` type
- **Never** include `healthyReferenceImage` in list responses — reference images are internet-sourced and must not appear in user-facing list cards

## Data Rules
- Normalize high-value app fields into columns on `plant_analyses`
- Store raw model output in `rawModelResponseJsonb JSONB`
- Histories (`watering`, `fertilizer`, `prune`) are first-class tables, not embedded JSON
- Analysis status lifecycle: `PENDING → PROCESSING → COMPLETED | FAILED`

## Reminder Recompute Triggers
Recompute `PlantReminderState` whenever:
- Watering event recorded
- Fertilizer event recorded
- Prune event recorded
- Registration analysis completes
- Reanalysis completes
- Scheduled periodic recompute runs

## Prompt Storage Rules
- Prompt body stored as `TEXT`, never `VARCHAR(n)`
- `llm_prompts` table holds versioned reusable templates with `prompt_key`, `version`, `role`
- `llm_requests` table audits every rendered prompt sent to the model + response
- `OpenAiPlantClient` must write to `llm_requests` on every call

## Coding Standards
- Thin controllers, richer services
- Explicit DTOs — no entity leakage to API layer
- Clear `@Transactional` boundaries
- `@Valid` bean validation on request bodies
- Good `@Slf4j` logging at service and worker boundaries
- Interfaces for all external dependencies
- Avoid framework magic when explicit code is clearer
- Spring profiles: `local` uses `LocalImageStorageService` + `LocalPlantJobPublisher`; `prod` uses S3 + SQS
